Glad to see this site is still up.<br>
I was on the Vietnam Challenge making a film of the event with Kartemquin film for Sports Ilustrated TV.  The other filmakers in the Team were Peter Gilbert, Jerry Blumenthal, Adam Singer, and Jim Fetterly. The 2 hour special on the event should be broadcast this Spring.  David Lambs pieces catch the flavor of the event.  The Vets who rode dispalyed great courage and are the ones who are leading the way to healing the past wounds and building bridges between our 2 countries.<br><br>
check out for more info ans pix from the ride.<br><br>
http://www.askasia.org/gateway_to_asia/gta_frm6.htm<br><br>
You are right about the Sorrow of War<br><br>
I also found When Heven and Earth Changed places (the book by Le Ly Hayslip not the explotive movie by Oliver Stone) to be a good introduction to some the the issues you are raising
